content:
Block sensitive data in Enhanced Messaging, Messaging for In-App and Web, and Voice transcripts. Set up rules to hide particular data patterns, such as credit card numbers or profanity, by removing or replacing the text with custom text like "(credit card number)". This change applies to enhanced Messaging channels, Messaging for In-App and Web, and Voice.

To create a sensitive data rule, go to Setup > Sensitive Data Rules for Enhanced Channels page. Click New Rule, provide the text patterns, define scope and behavior, and turn on the Sensitive Data Rules setting when ready to enforce rules.
title: Block Sensitive Data in Enhanced Messaging
